brewery.brewery_description:
Defying the odds isn’t just what we do, it’s a part of our DNA. We were founded by a woman in 1867. Lived through two wars. Survived a fire. Overcame the Halifax Explosion. Competed as an independent company against breweries 100 times our size. We haven’t just survived - we’ve thrived. And while others back down, we outlast.

Moosehead Breweries Limited is the last major brewery in Canada still owned by Canadians.

The brewery is located in Saint John, New Brunswick and operates with values that have been safely guarded by the same family for 148 years.

Despite obstacles – devastating fires, Prohibition, the Great Depression, two world wars, obstructive trade barriers, and bruising competition from breweries 100 times its size – Moosehead is one of the most durable and long lasting companies in Canada. Ultimately it has been the Oland family’s passion for beer that has enabled them to be successful over the long term.

With their product on beer shelves from the Maritimes to B.C., and its flagship Moosehead Lager shipped to approximately 350 distributors in the U.S.; Moosehead has become an iconic mainstay in North America’s beer industry.

Moosehead forges its own path in the beer landscape. So when it comes to crafting a radler, it’s no different. Moosehead Radler is based on our award-winning lager recipe but features hits of natural grapefruit, grape and lemon juices to round out a truly unique taste profile.

Developed with 15% real juice and brewed to 4% alcohol by volume Moosehead Radler offers more kick than its radler counterparts.

The beer that built the brewery.  Moosehead Pale Ale was our first beer good enough to be called Moosehead.  ‘Moose Red’ as it’s referred to in the Maritimes has a loyal following who appreciate its remarkably smooth, European-influenced taste.

This ultra premium light lager is dedicated to life’s most relaxed moments. 
Because life’s better when you paddle slower.
Get outside and reconnect, with a beer that’s as real as it gets. This classic refreshing lager is light-coloured, medium-bodied, and brewed with Styrian Golding and Nugget hops.
Our emphasis on quality and traditional craftsmanship gives Moose Light a crisp and refreshing taste that finishes extremely smooth. It also helped us earn a win at the renowned World Beer Cup.
5.5 is the most popular sibling in the beer family. The Alec Baldwin or Michael Jackson of J.R. beers. (Sorry Tito.) Find this dry, yet mildly spicy lager anywhere people with good taste sell beer.

Hazy, juicy, East Coast IPA's have dominated the craft scene. A blend of tropical hops deliver a balance of citrus tropical aromas and soft fruity flavours. This young but easy to drink style is loved by beer fans and rises to any occasion.

A juicy, citrusy IPA with tropical hop flavours and lactose sugar that balances the bitterness. A generous amount of strawberry and rhubarb were added to the fermentation to give the beer a strong fruit back bone that's subtly sweet and yet a little tart.

Moosehead Watermelon Radler is based on our award-winner lager recipe infused with a hit of natural watermelon and apple juice making it exceptionally drinkable and the perfect drink for summer.

Developed with 15% real juice and brewed to 4% alcohol by volume, Watermelon Radler is the perfect addition to the Moosehead Radler family.

Our award-winning lager combines with peach and mango juices for a taste that’s refreshingly different. Developed with 15% real juice and brewed to 4% alcohol by volume, this fan favourite is perfect for summer.

Our award-winning lager combines with lemonade and strawberry juice for a taste that’s refreshingly different. Developed with 15% real juice and brewed to 4% alcohol by volume, Strawberry Lemonade Radler is the perfect addition to the Moosehead Radler family.

Our Peppermint IPA is perfect to kick-off the holiday season. A well-balanced brew with the addition of dried peppermint leaves during the final minutes of brewing gives it a subtle peppermint flavour that lingers. It has a smooth mouthfeel and is clear pale gold in colour. This festive brew is complimented by the inclusion of Fuggles and Northern Brewer hops, which have a slightly minty flavour.

Full-bodied and smooth, our Export Stout has a slightly roasted malt aroma with a delightful coffee and dark chocolate flavour. It was first brewed in 1929 and was brought back as part of our Heritage Series. The new packaging was inspired by the crowns of English monarchs from the Tudor period to the end of the English monarchy – with the overturned crowns representing Lady Jane Grey and Charles I.

This light, well-balanced amber ale has a modest hop flavour and is a malt forward ale of the highest quality. This brew’s name goes way back. Old Stock Ale in England used to be priced according to the quality and strength, so a few cents would get you a cheap ale...but a Ten Penny would get you the highest quality. Ten Penny Stock Ale was first brewed in 1934 and is a Moosehead classic.
Moosehead dry ice has a reputation for being a drinkable strong beer. A clean beer with european hop aroma, dry ice is a well-balanced beer.
Our Mango IPA is a hazy, juicy, tropical hop explosion in a glass. This brew has a velvety smooth mouthfeel and is highly aromatic from the mangoes and citrusy hops.

Brewed with real Canadian honey. Our Prairie Honey Wheat Ale is a medium-bodied, well-balanced brew that is the perfect drink for a hot summer day. The honey malt leaves notes of residual sweetness that is rounded out with a slight hop bitterness, resulting in a refreshing brew all around.

A deep, dark, and delectable lager. This deliciously robust black lager features notes of coffee and cocoa infused with pure Quebec maple syrup as part of our Canadian Home Grown Series. Two Canadian super powers of maple syrup and beer are blended together seamlessly to create a delicious beer with a slightly sweet finish.

Celtic myth has tales of kings being served Red ale ladled from silver vats. Our Irish Red Ale is served from a can, but we believe our malt-forward brew with caramel and toffee notes is just as fit for royalty.

Citrus, spice and everything nice. Peel into our refreshing and zesty Belgian style Tangerine Witbier. This naturally cloudy brew with a subtle sweetness pairs perfectly with those lazy, hazy summer days.

Scratch #36 is a West Coast IPA! This India Pale Ale is bursting with pine and citrus hop aromas. Copious amounts of Centennial, Cascade, Amarillo, and Simcoe hops were added to the brewing process for maximum hop flavour, and the brew was heavily dry-hopped to create an aromatic beer. Our West Coast IPA pours a bright amber in colour and has small, tight bubbles before finishing dry.
